President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. Christopher P. Lu is nominated for Deputy Secretary of the Department of Labor. Michael W. Kempner is nominated for Member of the Broadcasting Board of Governors. Wes Moore is nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the Corporation for National and Community Service. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Robert D. Alverson, James W. Balsiger, and Donald R. Lane as United States Commissioners to the International Pacific Halibut Commission. These individuals bring a wealth of talent and expertise to their new roles, and President Obama looks forward to working with them in the future.